# ── Local dev (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Socket.io + REST base URL (no trailing slash). If unset, uses http://localhost:3001
# VITE_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:3001

# ── Production / Vercel (no dashboard needed for the API URL) ───
#
# Edit `client/.env.production` (committed in repo): set VITE_SERVER_URL to your public
# game server. Push = next Vercel build picks it up.
#
# Optional: override at runtime only — set SERVER_URL on Vercel or use `/api/server-url`.
#
# Optional: `src/config/productionServerUrl.ts` → FALLBACK_PRODUCTION_SERVER_URL

# ── QA / E2E test hooks (window.__a2a.test + ?qa=1 per-tab isolation) ──
# Enables the A2A test hooks used by the 2-client runbook. Auto-on in local dev
# (`npm run dev`). For a deployed test target, set VITE_QA_HOOKS=1 on a PREVIEW
# build only. Leave UNSET in production — the hooks (incl. consent-bypassing
# autoAcceptPairs) are dead-code-eliminated from the production bundle.
# On Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables → VITE_QA_HOOKS=1,
# scoped to the "Preview" environment (NOT Production).
# VITE_QA_HOOKS=1
